snippet: The cracked turbine blade found in a single engine resulted from overuse during testing, officials said, and all other fighter jets were unaffected.
abstract: Pentagon lifts its grounding of the new F-35 jet fighter after concluding that a turbine blade had cracked on only a single plane after it was overused in test operations.
lead_paragraph: The cracked turbine blade found in a single engine resulted from overuse during testing, officials said, and all other fighter jets were unaffected.
